Hey,

I don&#39;t know that it&#39;s documented. :-&#92; I noticed this in
PreconditionEnforcer.credentialPrecondition() which told me that the form

action url had to be queued for crawling one way or another:

        if (c.isPrerequisite(curi)) { ... }

ExtractorHTML has the setting extractOnlyFormGets which is true by default.
You&#39;d probably also get the url if you set that to false, and leave
ignoreFormActionUrls with its default value of false.

We use ExtractorHTMLForms+FormLoginProcessor for archive-it.org so I have
more experience with

them than with HTMLFormCredential.

Noah


